				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The obvious advantage of the top-left corner are:<br />-easy to read sprite tables<br />-top-left sprite of the metasprite is always positioned 1:1 with the metasprite itself.<br /><br />I think many games are using radiuses and center-positioned origins/anchors. If a metasprite has a square hitbox, one radius would be sufficient. But normally, you'd have xrad and yrad. <br /><br />center positions ought to make directional flips easier. <br /><br />it may be comfortable to keep the y anchor at the bottom of the metasprite in a platformer, but you don't have to.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.frankengraphics.com">http://www.frankengraphics.com</a><!-- m --> - personal NES blog</div>
